Kano State House of Assembly on Wednesday commenced debate on the motion for the creation of four additional emirates in the state. It would be recalled that at the plenary yesterday, the motion has passed the first reading, just as the lawmakers are expected to debate on the motion today for the second and third readings respectively. The house is expected to finish its job today and forward the bill to the State Governor, Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje for his assent. Kano lawmakers set to approve 4 new emirates Kano: Motion for creation of four new emirates passes 1st reading Tight security at Kano Assembly as lawmakers set to amend Emirate council law Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin